    "notes": [
      "Two-player JS oracle backup for head-head-looking same-endpoint movement under reverse source avatar update order.",
      "p1 updates first, reaches (44,44), emits a normal point body, and survives because its own fresh body is ignored by own-trail latency.",
      "p0 updates second, reaches the same endpoint, emits its own normal point, then dies to p1's same-frame emitted point body.",
      "The live p1 head alone is not a collision body; this fixture proves the source order asymmetry comes from synchronous point insertion, not a symmetric live-head collision rule.",
      "Forced trail state makes initial printing a direct runtime state and avoids setup-time printManager.start() point side effects."
    ]
  },
